《'''創造亞當'''》 是[[米開朗基羅|米開朗基羅]]創作的[[西斯汀小堂|西斯汀小堂]]天頂畫《[[創世紀_(壁畫)|創世紀]]》的一部分，創作於1511至1512年間的[[文藝復興全盛期|文藝復興全盛期]]。這幅壁畫描繪的是《[[創世紀|聖經·創世紀]]》中上帝創造人類始祖[[亞當|亞當]]的情形，按照事情發展順序是創世紀天頂畫中的第四幅。作為世界名畫之一，後世出現了許多《創造亞當》的仿作。

==內容==
畫中右側穿著飄逸長袍的白鬍鬚老者是上帝，亞當則位於畫面左側，通身赤裸。上帝的右臂舒張開來，生命之火從他的指頭中傳遞給了亞當，而後者則以同樣的方式舒展左臂，含蓄地指出人類是按照上帝的模樣來創造的。關於上帝周圍的形象有許多臆測，例如抱著上帝左臂的可能是[[夏娃|夏娃]]，但也有可能是[[聖母瑪利亞|聖母瑪利亞]]，或者可能只是一個單純的女性天使。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Steinberg|first1=Leo|date=December 1992|title=Who's who in Michelangelo's ''Creation of Adam'': A Chronology of the Picture's Reluctant Self-Revelation|journal=[[College_Art_Association|The Art Bulletin]]|volume=74|issue=4|pages=553–554|jstor=3045910|url=http://www.ecfs.org/projects/fieldston272/Readings/SteinbergMichelCreation.pdf|accessdate=April 9, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407074813/http://www.ecfs.org/projects/fieldston272/Readings/SteinbergMichelCreation.pdf|archivedate=2012年4月7日}}</ref> 

===解读===
1990年，美國[[印第安納州|印第安納州]][[安德森_(印第安納州)|安德森]]的一位醫生在《[[美國醫學會雜誌|美國醫學會雜誌]]》（署名Frank Meshberger, M.D.）上撰文稱上帝周圍的形象實際上是一副[[人腦|人腦]]解剖圖<ref name=Meshberger>{{cite journal |last1=Meshberger |first1=Frank Lynn |date=October 10, 1990 |title=An Interpretation of Michelangelo's Creation of Adam Based on Neuroanatomy |journal=JAMA |volume=264 |issue=14 |pages=1837–41 |publisher= |doi=10.1001/jama.1990.03450140059034 |pmid=2205727 |pmc= |url=http://jama.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=383532 |accessdate=September 24, 2012 |archive-date=2016-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160906054107/http://jama.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=383532 |dead-url=no }} [http://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=1229086804171881877 Pdf] {{Wayback|url=http://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=1229086804171881877 |date=20160419111813 }}. [http://www.mentalhealthandillness.com/creation_fr.html Excerpt] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mentalhealthandillness.com/creation_fr.html |date=20200130210452 }} on Mental Health & Illness.com. Retrieved September 21, 2010.</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Appler |first1=Mark Lee |date=March 6, 1991 |title=The Creation of Adam: Divine Funster Decrees We Are What We Eat: Chicken? |journal=Letters in comment: JAMA |volume=265 |issue=9 |pages=1111 |publisher= |doi=10.1001/jama.1991.03460090059025 |pmid=1995993 |pmc= |url=http://jama.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=385198 |accessdate=September 24, 2012 |archive-date=2016-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307213049/http://jama.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=385198 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。其中包括[[端腦|端腦]]的[[腦溝|腦溝]]、[[腦幹|腦幹]]、[[額葉|額葉]]、[[基底動脈|基底動脈]]、[[腦下垂體|腦下垂體]]和[[視神經交叉|視神經交叉]]<ref name=Meshberger/>。

除去大腦說外，也有藝術史學家認為上帝的紅袍正好形成了一個人類[[子宮|子宮]]<ref>{{cite book|first=Adrian|last=Stokes|title=Michelangelo. A study in the nature of art|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=MqRPAAAAMAAJ|year=1955|publisher=[[Tavistock_Institute|Tavistock Publications]]|location=[[倫敦城市大學|City University London]]|page=[http://books.google.com/books?id=MqRPAAAAMAAJ&q=%22uterine+mantle%22%22The+Creation+of+Adam%22 89]|access-date=2014-10-24|archive-date=2016-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160419131902/https://books.google.com/books?id=MqRPAAAAMAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>，飄飛的綠色緞帶則可能是代表[[臍帶|臍帶]]<ref>{{cite book |last=Bruschini |first=Enrico |title=Masterpieces of the Vatican |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=O7QzAQAAIAAJ |year=2004 |publisher=Edizioni Musei Vaticani |location=Vatican City |id=ISBN 88-811-7088-4; ISBN 978-8-881-17088-3 |access-date=2014-10-24 |archive-date=2020-08-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819164115/https://books.google.com/books?id=O7QzAQAAIAAJ |dead-url=no }} p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=O7QzAQAAIAAJ&q=%22recently+an+American+gynaecologist,+observing+the+profile+of+the+red+mantle,+noted+an+outstanding+resemblance+to+the+human+uterus.+The+green+cord+trailing+below+the+mantle+corresponds+exactly+with+an+umbilical+cord+that+has+just+been+cut.%22 112] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=O7QzAQAAIAAJ&q=%22recently+an+American+gynaecologist,+observing+the+profile+of+the+red+mantle,+noted+an+outstanding+resemblance+to+the+human+uterus.+The+green+cord+trailing+below+the+mantle+corresponds+exactly+with+an+umbilical+cord+that+has+just+been+cut.%22 |date=20160419101306 }}.</ref><ref>Bruschini, Enrico (2004). p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=O7QzAQAAIAAJ&q=%22This+is+an+interesting+hypothesis+that+presents+the+Creation+scene+as+an+idealised+representation+of+the+physical+birth+of+man.+It+explains+the+navel+that+appears+on+Adam,+which+is+at+first+perplexing+because+he+was+created,+not+born+of+a+woman.%22 112] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=O7QzAQAAIAAJ&q=%22This+is+an+interesting+hypothesis+that+presents+the+Creation+scene+as+an+idealised+representation+of+the+physical+birth+of+man.+It+explains+the+navel+that+appears+on+Adam,+which+is+at+first+perplexing+because+he+was+created,+not+born+of+a+woman.%22 |date=20160419152048 }}.</ref>。

==來源==
米開朗基羅畫中亞當形象可能是來自一個雕有[[奧古斯都|奧古斯都]]騎著[[摩羯宮|摩羯]]的[[多彩寶石浮雕|多彩寶石浮雕]]<ref>[http://www.google.com/search?num=100&safe=off&q=Augustus+cameo+Capricorn&tbm=isch&tbs=simg:CAQSWxpZCxCo1NgEGgQIAAgDDAsQsIynCBowCi4IARIIyQfPB1xU2AcaIPnWk4lKOU8m2nuJ-Em0x5WviHRTdHCMVbX3tZKbc74nDAsQjq7-CBoKCggIARIEsQs9AAw Cameo] {{Wayback|url=http://www.google.com/search?num=100&safe=off&q=Augustus+cameo+Capricorn&tbm=isch&tbs=simg:CAQSWxpZCxCo1NgEGgQIAAgDDAsQsIynCBowCi4IARIIyQfPB1xU2AcaIPnWk4lKOU8m2nuJ-Em0x5WviHRTdHCMVbX3tZKbc74nDAsQjq7-CBoKCggIARIEsQs9AAw |date=20150924164513 }} on Google Image.</ref>，這個浮雕現藏於英國[[諾森伯蘭郡|諾森伯蘭郡]][[阿尼克城堡|阿尼克城堡]]<ref>{{cite journal | last=Sutherland | first=Bruce | date=Winter 2013 | title=Cameo Appearances on the Sistine Ceiling | journal=Source: Notes in the History of Art | volume=32 | issue=2 | page=14 | publisher=Ars Brevis Foundation, Inc. | jstor=23292907}} Alnwick Castle is in Northumberland, not Northampton, as the captions state. The Duke of Northumberland who owns the cameos discussed in the article has expressed his appreciation in a letter to the author.</ref>。這件藝術品原本是{{link-en|道明·格里曼尼|Domenico Grimani}}[[樞機|樞機]]的藏品，他在米開朗基羅繪製《創造亞當》時正好住在羅馬，且有證據顯示二人頗有交情。但也有說法稱亞當的形象實際上是來自於[[洛倫佐·吉貝爾蒂|洛倫佐·吉貝爾蒂]]同名作品中的亞當<ref>Sutherland, Bruce (Winter 2013). pp. 12-18.</ref>。此外，米開朗基羅的關於上帝與亞當互相向對方伸出手臂的創作靈感也許是來自[[中世紀|中世紀]][[聖詩|聖詩]]《[[輕叩心扉之門|輕叩心扉之門]]》（Veni Creator Spiritus）<ref>[http://www.preces-latinae.org/thesaurus/Hymni/VeniCreator.html Veni, Creator Spiritus / Come Holy Spirit, Creator Blest] {{Wayback|url=http://www.preces-latinae.org/thesaurus/Hymni/VeniCreator.html |date=20201022114534 }}. Preces-latinae.org.</ref>。

==流行文化==
[[File:Touched_by_His_Noodly_Appendage_HD.jpg|thumb]]的标志之一]]
作為最出名的藝術作品之一，《創造亞當》有眾多的仿作<ref name=Smithsonian>{{cite web | url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/arts-culture/The-Measure-of-Genius-Michelangelos-Sistine-Chapel-at-500.html | title=The Measure of Genius | first=Jamie | last=Katz | date=10 April 2009 | work=[[Smithsonian_(magazine)|Smithsonian.com]] | accessdate=13 September 2013 | archive-date=2013-12-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203165309/http://www.smithsonianmag.com/arts-culture/The-Measure-of-Genius-Michelangelos-Sistine-Chapel-at-500.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，較著名者包括約翰·阿爾文為《[[E.T.外星人|E.T.外星人]]》所繪的海報<ref name=Smithsonian/><ref name=Pop>{{cite web |url=http://www.bitrebels.com/geek/pop-culture-art-inspired-by-michelangelos-the-creation-of-adam | title=Pop Culture Art Inspired By Michelangelo's ''The Creation Of Adam'' | first=Nuno | last=Teixeira |work=bitrebels.com | accessdate=13 September 2013}}</ref>。《[[辛普森一家|辛普森一家]]》、《[[布偶大電影|布偶大電影]]》、《[[芝麻街|芝麻街]]》和《[[發展受阻|發展受阻]]》等許多影視作品中也可以見到這幅畫的身影。[[頑強的D|頑強的D]]的專輯《[[搖滾之神|搖滾之神]]》的封面和《[[冒牌天神|冒牌天神]]》的电影海报也是《創造亞當》的[[戲仿|戲仿]]。

2005年8月，瑞典设计师尼克拉斯·简森（Niklas Jansson）创作了一副「可以在出版物及我能想到的其他范围内随意使用」的图画，恶搞了[[米开朗琪罗|米开朗琪罗]]的名作《[[创世纪_(壁画)|创世纪]]》中的一幅作品《创造亚当》，用飞行面条怪替换了[[耶和华|耶和华]]的位置。这幅恶搞画作已经成为[[飞天意面神|-{zh:飞行面条;zh-sg:飞行面条;zh-tw:飛天義大利麵;zh-hk:飛天意粉怪;zh-cn:飞天意面神;}-信仰]]的标志。<ref name="Ha Ha, Only Serious">{{cite web|url=https://scholarsbank.uoregon.edu/xmlui/handle/1794/9336|title=Ha Ha, Only Serious: A Preliminary Study of Joke Religions |last=Narizny|first=Laurel|date=October 2009|work=Department of Religious Studies And the Honors College of the University of Oregon|publisher=University of Oregon|pages=42–49|accessdate=2009-11-25}}</ref>

